    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Deseed your <strong>pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thin strips</p><p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>red onion[s]</strong></p><p>Boil half a kettle</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/hake-pepper-and-lemongrass-curry-with-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick, with a matching lid) with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Add the <strong>pepper strips</strong> and <strong>sliced onion</strong> with a big pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Cook for 5 min, then reduce the heat to low and cook for 10-15 min or until softened and caramelised</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/hake-pepper-and-lemongrass-curry-with-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, place your<strong> creamed</strong> <strong>coconut</strong> (in its packaging!) in a mug and cover with <strong>boiled water</strong> (this softens the naturally hard cream)</p><p>Peel your <strong>ginger</strong> (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and your <strong>garlic</strong>, then finely chop (or grate) both</p><p>Bash your <strong>lemongrass stalk[s]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>with a <strong>rolling pin</strong>, cut it down the middle lengthways, remove the <strong>tough</strong> <strong>outer layers</strong> and set aside for later, then chop the <strong>soft inner core[s]</strong> finely</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/hake-pepper-and-lemongrass-curry-with-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>white</strong> <strong>long grain rice</strong> to a pot with a lid with 225ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[450ml] </span><strong>cold water</strong> and the<strong> outer lemongrass</strong> <strong>layers </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving \u2013 this is your <strong>lemongrass rice</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/hake-pepper-and-lemongrass-curry-with-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped ginger</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic</strong>,<strong> chopped lemongrass core[s]</strong>, <strong>curry powder</strong> and<strong> black sesame seeds</strong> to the onion pan and cook for 2 min</p><p>Chop your <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/hake-pepper-and-lemongrass-curry-with-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>On a clean board, chop your<strong> hake fillet[s]</strong> into large bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[260ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [350ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong>, the <strong>softened creamed coconut </strong>and your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> to the pan and stir for 2 min until everything has combined, then gently add the <strong>chopped hake</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/hake-pepper-and-lemongrass-curry-with-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Bring to the boil over a high heat, once boiling, reduce to medium and cook, covered for 5 min, or until cooked through \u2013 this is your <strong>hake, pepper & lemongrass curry</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked when it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/hake-pepper-and-lemongrass-curry-with-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Stir<strong> half</strong> the <strong>chopped coriander</strong> through the <strong>hake, pepper & lemongrass curry</strong> and serve over the <strong>lemongrass rice</strong>, discard the <strong>lemongrass</strong></p><p>Garnish with the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>coriander</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
